<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278748>
    dc:description "PLATE 106. A. Gonatopus longicollis, female from Spain. Length 4.8 mm (from Olmi 1999a). B. G. asiaticus, holotype. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278748/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278756>
    dc:description "PLATE 108. A. Gonatopus pedestris, female from Italy, lateral view. Length 3.0 mm. B. Mesosoma, lateral view of G. rufoniger (=G. indianus Olmi), from India. Length 2.0 mm. C. Female of G. bicolor, lateral view. Lenght 2.9 mm. D. G. acuminatus, holotype, lateral view. Length 3.12 mm. (From Olmi 1984)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278756/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278712>
    dc:description "PLATE 96. Neodryinus malayanus, female holotype (from Olmi 1991). Length 5.0 mm. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278712/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278728>
    dc:description "PLATE 100. Echthrodelphax fairchildii. A, B. Female in dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.5 mm. C. Chela of female from Japan. Scale bar 0.16 mm for C. (From Olmi 1984)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278728/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278702>
    dc:description "PLATE 93. Chelae. A. Neodryinus dolosus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). B. N. grandis, holotype (Xu et al. 2011a). C. N. isoneurus, holotype (from Xu & He, 1997e). D. N. javanus, female from Malaysia (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.37 mm for A and C, 0.31 mm for B and D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278702/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278752>
    dc:description "PLATE 107. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus paulyi (from Olmi 1986). B. G.abjectus (from Olmi 1984). C. G. bengalensis (from Olmi 1984). D. G. lucens (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.15 mm for A, 0.14 mm for B, 0.21 mm for C and 0.20 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278752/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278706>
    dc:description "PLATE 94. Neodryinus javanus, Male. Length 3.4 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278706/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278762>
    dc:description "PLATE 110. Gonatopus nearcticus (=Acrodontochelys ugandanus (Benoit)), male from Uganda. Length 3.0 mm (from Olmi 1984). A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278762/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278796>
    dc:description "PLATE 121. Gonatopus flavifemur. A. Female from Viet Nam. Length 3.0 mm. B. Chela of female from Japan (from Olmi 1984). C. Male (=Dicondylus indianus Olmi) from India (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.6 mm. Scale bar 0.20 mm for B." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278796/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278708>
    dc:description "PLATE 95. A, B. Male genitalia. C. Pronotum in lateral view, holotype. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Neodryinus javanus from Malaya (from Olmi 1984). B. N. karaentensis, holotype (from Olmi 2011a). C, D. N. leptopus (from Olmi 1984). E. N. lineatus (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.21 mm for B, 1.19 mm for C, 0.29 mm for D and E." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278708/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278782>
    dc:description "PLATE 117. A–C. Male genitalia. D, H. Chelae, holotypse. E. Head. F, G. Mesosoma. A. Gonatopus nudus from Malaya. B. G. sarawakensis or malesiae, var. a. C. G. sarawakensis or malesiae, var. b. D. G. sarawakensis. E, F, H. G. validus. G. G. validus, female from China. Scale bar 0.24 mm for A, 0.27 mm for B, 0.29 mm for C, 0.16 mm for D, 0.12 mm for H. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278782/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278800>
    dc:description "PLATE 122. A. Male, lateral view. B–D. Male genitalia. E. Chela, holotype. A. Gonatopus flavifemur (=Dicondylus indianus Olmi) from India. Length 2.6 mm. B. G. flavifemur from Australia. C. G. lucens from Japan. D. G. pedestris from Finland. E. G. lucens. Scale bar 0.17 mm for B, 0.10 mm for C, 0.15 mm for D and 0.19 mm for E. (From Olmi 1984)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278800/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278734>
    dc:description "PLATE 102. A, B, E, F. Male genitalia. C, D. Chelae. A. Echthrodelphax fairchildii from Hawaii (from Olmi 1984). B, C. E. laotianus from Thailand (from Olmi 1998e). C. E. laotianus, holotype (from Olmi 1984). D. E. rufus, paratype (arolium removed) (from Olmi 1984). E, F. E. rufus from China, paramere in ventral side (E) and dorsal view (F) (from Olmi 1995a). Scale bar 0.13 mm for A, 0.08 mm for B, 0.14 mm for C, 0.11 mm for D, E and F." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278730>
    dc:description "PLATE 101. Echthrodelphax fairchildii, males from Hawaii, Oahu, Ewa (from Olmi 1984). Length 1.8 mm. A. Dorsal view. B. Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5278730/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

